BioWorld Marketplace enables serious IDE modding—players buy/sell extensions, pipelines, datasets—with $10/month seller tier (90/10 split), pure science progression (no cash rewards, just validated contributions), and strict anti‑cheat bans.[1]

## Marketplace Model

| Tier | Cost | Features | Revenue Share |
|------|------|----------|---------------|
| Free Buyer | $0 | Browse/buy tools, limited bounties. | N/A |
| $5 Player | $5/mo | Premium missions, credit boosts. | N/A |
| $10 Seller | $10/mo | List/sell mods, 90% revenue (you take 10%), priority search. | 90% to seller |
| Lab Sponsor | Custom | Bulk buys, branded initiatives. | Negotiated |

- **No cash science rewards**: Progress = peer‑reviewed contributions (e.g., "Validated Cas9 pipeline, +500 XP"). Cheating (fake data) = auto‑ban via anomaly detection.[2]
- **Anti‑manipulation**: Server‑side validation for all submits; bans for undermining (e.g., spam listings).

